ime News Network |accessdate=December 26, 2018 |date=December 26, 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Rui|\u30eb\u30a4|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Kenn (Japanese actor)|KENN]]}}<ref name=\"april\" /> (Japanese); Howard Wang (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Sumire|\u30b9\u30df\u30ec|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Natsumi Hioka]]}}<ref name=\"april\" /> (Japanese); Macy Anne Johnson (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Taiy\u014d|\u30bf\u30a4\u30e8\u30a6|}}\n:{{Voiced by|Hidenori Takahashi}}<ref name=\"cast3\">{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Anime Reveals 7th Visual, 2 More Cast Members |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-07/shometsu-toshi-anime-reveals-7th-visual-2-more-cast-members/.143106 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=February 7, 2019 |date=February 7, 2019}}</ref> (Japanese); [[Mike McFarland]] (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Tsuki|\u30c4\u30ad|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Asami Imai]]}}<ref name=\"cast3\" /> (Japanese); [[Lydia Mackay]] (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Y\u016bji|\u30e6\u30a6\u30b8|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Ry\u014dta Suzuki (voice actor)|Ry\u014dta Suzuki]]}}<ref name=\"cast4\">{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Anime Reveals 3 More Cast Members |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-21/shometsu-toshi-anime-reveals-3-more-cast-members/.143724 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=February 21, 2019 |date=February 21, 2019}}</ref> (Japanese); Garret Storms (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Keigo|\u30b1\u30a4\u30b4|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Masaki Terasoma]]}}<ref name=\"cast4\"/> (Japanese); [[David Wald]] (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Shunpei|\u30b7\u30e5\u30f3\u30da\u30a4|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Yoshitaka Yamaya]]}}<ref name=\"cast4\"/> (Japanese); Aaron Roberts (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Jack|\u30b8\u30e3\u30c3\u30af|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Atsushi Imaruoka]]}}<ref name=\"cast5\">{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Anime Reveals 2 More Cast Members, April 7 Premiere|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-02-28/shometsu-toshi-anime-reveals-2-more-cast-members-april-7-premiere/.144006|website=Anime News Network |accessdate=February 28, 2019 |date=February 28, 2019}}</ref> (Japanese); Christopher Guerrero (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n;{{Nihongo|Kana|\u30ab\u30ca|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Yurika Kubo]]}}<ref name=\"cast5\"/> (Japanese)\n\n;{{Nihongo|Kaibara|\u30ab\u30a4\u30d0\u30e9|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Tessh\u014d Genda]]}}<ref name=\"cast6\">{{cite web |last1=Loo |first1=Egan |title=Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Anime Casts Tessh\u014d Genda, Kenjiro Tsuda|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-03-21/shometsu-toshi-anime-casts-tessho-genda-kenjiro-tsuda/.144805|website=Anime News Network |accessdate=March 21, 2019 |date=March 21, 2019}}</ref> (Japanese)\n\n;{{Nihongo|Daichi|\u30c0\u30a4\u30c1|}}\n:{{Voiced by|[[Kenjiro Tsuda]]}}<ref name=\"cast6\"/> (Japanese); Christopher Wehkemp (English)<ref name=\"dub cast\" />\n\n==Media==\n===Game===\nWright Flyer Studios and [[GREE, Inc.|GREE]] launched the original [[mobile game]] in May 2014, and an update titled ''Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi 2'' was released in November 2016.<ref name=\"anime\">{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-05-27/shometsu-toshi-smartphone-game-gets-tv-anime-at-madhouse/.132080 |title=Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Smartphone Game Gets TV Anime at Madhouse (Updated) |last=Hodgkins |first=Crystalyn |date=May 27, 2018 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=May 27, 2018 }}</ref> As revealed in the live broadcast held on November 13, 2018, ''Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi 0.'', the third update to the game, will be available for download on the evening of the latest music concert to be held on November 25. A new mobile game, titled ''Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Drama RPG MIX'', is in production, as is an unspecified 3D project powered by [[Unreal Engine|Unreal Engine 4]].<ref name=\"anime\" />\n\n===Anime===\nAn [[anime]] television series adaptation was announced on May 27, 2018.<ref name=\"anime\" />  The series was animated by [[Madhouse (company)|Madhouse]], directed by Shigeyuki Miya, and written by Shingo Irie.<ref name=\"staff\" /><ref name=\"anime\" />  Tomoyuki Shitaya designed the characters, while Satoshi Motoyama served as the series' sound director.<ref name=\"staff\" /> [[Kenji Kawai]] composed the series' music,<ref name=\"staff\" /> which was produced by [[Pony Canyon]].<ref name=\"anime\" /> The series aired from April 7 to June 23, 2019 on [[Tokyo MX]], [[Yomiuri Telecasting Corporation|ytv]], [[Nippon BS Broadcasting|BS11]], and [[AT-X (company)|AT-X]].<ref name=\"Premiere\" /><ref name=\"april\" /> [[Mao Abe]] performed the series' opening theme song \"Kotae\". For the ending theme, Hanazawa performed a cover of \"[[Swallowtail Butterfly (Ai no Uta)|Swallowtail Butterfly \uff5eAi no Uta\uff5e]]\" by [[Chara (singer)|Chara]] for the first two episodes and a cover of \"[[Hello, Again (Mukashi Kara Aru Basho)|Hello, Again \uff5eMukashi Kara Aru Basho\uff5e]]\" by [[My Little Lover]] in episodes 8 and 12, while SPR5 performed \"With Your Breath\" from episodes 3-7, then episodes 9-11.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Sherman |first1=Jennifer |title=Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Anime's Opening Video Previews Mao Abe Song|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-22/shometsu-toshi-anime-opening-video-previews-mao-abe-song/.142416|website=Anime News Network |accessdate=January 22, 2019 |date=January 22, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=Female Idol Unit SPR5 Perform Ending Theme for Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Anime|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-01-20/female-idol-unit-spr5-perform-ending-theme-for-shometsu-toshi-anime/.142318 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=January 20, 2019 |date=January 20, 2019}}</ref> The series ran for 12 episodes.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hodgkins |first1=Crystalyn |title=Sh\u014dmetsu Toshi Anime to Have 12 Episodes|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/daily-briefs/2019-03-25/shometsu-toshi-anime-to-have-12-episodes/.144996|website=Anime News Network |accessdate=March 25, 2019 |date=March 25, 2019}}</ref> The anime has been licensed by [[Funimation]], who premiered their [[simuldub]] on April 28, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.funimation.com/blog/2019/04/02/spring-2019-will-warm-you-up|title=Spring 2019 Will Warm You Up!|website=www.funimation.com|access-date=2019-04-13}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table |total_width=98 |overall= |title= |airdate= |overallT=No. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = Lost\n| TranslitTitle   = Sh\u014dmetsu\n| NativeTitle     = \u6d88\u6ec5\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|7}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = Sacrifice\n| TranslitTitle   = Gisei\n| NativeTitle     = \u72a0\u7272\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|14}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = Memory\n| TranslitTitle   = Kioku\n| NativeTitle     = \u8a18\u61b6\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|21}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 4\n| Title           = Suspicion\n| TranslitTitle   = Giwaku\n| NativeTitle     = \u7591\u60d1\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|28}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 5\n| Title           = Affection\n| TranslitTitle   = J\u014dai\n| NativeTitle     = \u60c5\u7231\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|5|5}}\n| ShortSummary    = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 6\n| Title           = Parting Ways\n| TranslitTitle   = Ketsubetsu\n| NativeTitle     = \u8a23\u5225\n| NativeTitleLangCode = ja \n|